d/druid/necro/shaman?/chanter) using pumice on the pet will remove it's first buff/debuff (read: the chamr hold). Once this is broken, the pet will no longer respond to the caster and in fact will be megataunted by the break of the charm enough to ignore just about anyone and take out the caster.<br>
<br>
This is really evil, and might be considered and exploit but I've never heard it confirmed. As far as I'm concerned it's as legitimate as a caster standing outside melee range but too close for range. So use at your discretion, but I certainly encourage it :)<br>
<br>
*Canbik grins evilly*<br>
